      "writtenOn": "2017-09-07T16:51:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I believe it\u0027s possible. I don\u0027t think we have been discarding paths based on the clip\u0027s bounds and/or the path\u0027s mapped device bounds? So if a GrClip returns something unexpectedly tight from getConservativeBounds, I think this could trip.\n\nIf we are mapping the path\u0027s bounds higher up on the stack, then maybe we should push it down here rather than recomputing it.",
      "parentUuid": "96698e26_4bd0edaa",
      "revId": "faf66938fbec34d76d0abce126a375d22b73aa40",
